\nc<>(There's no mistake. This is the power that the villains

\nc<>(Just being near them makes my breath stop...!)
\nc<>Isn't it amazing? I'm called the \C[1]Seed of Evil\c[0].

\nc<>This is what they call the origin of the villains in this
town, so to speak.

\nc<>For now, it is sealed. Well, if it's in that state, it's
only a matter of time before it's released.
\nc<>Why is such a terrifying thing underground in the town!?
\nc<>Well? I don't know the origin just by finding it myself.

\nc<>Wasn't there an incredibly powerful magical girl in the
distant past?
\nc<>For now, I understand why the sewer was unusually spacious.
\nc<>When I came, there was a small gap in the seal.

\nc<>It was quite dangerous in its own way, as the power inside
was about to overflow all at once and it seemed like it was
on the verge of exploding.

\nc<>If something like this were to explode, this town would be
completely blown away, meow...

\nc<>So, I tried to spread it on the surface as much as possible
while exerting as little power as possible, but the seal
only weakened.

\nc<>Since I also belong to the demon side, I can't erase it. I
was just stomping my feet in frustration.

\nc<>It was around that time when I found my senior who had come
to this town.

\nc<>They are much stronger than your typical magical girl, with
more experience and age, so their mental state is also
stable.

\nc<>So, you already understand what I want from my senior,
right?
\nc<>Yeah, we just need to defeat this person.

\nc<>Hold on, hold on, hold on, wait a minute! Even for Kei,
that's not an easy thing to do!

\nc<>First of all, if you're talking about magical girls, there
are other girls in different towns, meow!
\nc<>This seed of evil is the embodiment of human desires.

\nc<>Normal people would be tempted in an instant, and even
magical girls should receive considerable mental attacks.

\nc<>There may be strong children to some extent, and there may
be children with strong cores, but cases where both are
possessed are very few, right?

\nc<>Moreover, there's no way I can go searching for it,
especially when I need to regularly manage this power,
right?

\nc<>W-Well, that may be true, but... even so, this is just
too...

\nc<>It's okay, Cashew Nut. If it's Reina, they should have
already tried everything they can.

\nc<>...I said I would try earlier, but if I lose, it wouldn't
even be a conversation in the first place.

\nc<>I don't know if I can defeat the seed like my senior just
did. Even so, will you still help me?

\nc<>Leave it to me. Isn't it what being a hero is all about,
helping when someone asks for help?

\nc<>I will defeat this person and definitely restore the town
to its original state!
\nc<>Hehe. I thought my senior would say that.
